article.para: The DocBook roundtripping system supports only a subset of DocBook elements. The status of support for the various elements is shown below.
Further, DocBook elements may only be combined in certain ways. Restrictions to how elements may be used together is also noted below.
Legend: dbk:yes fully supported; dbk:no not supported; dbk:partial limited support.

entry.para: Will be included in component metadata. May be preceded by a title.
Address elements will be created where necessary in metadata, but mayalso be explicit.
Must be preceded by a question.
Must be preceded by an areaspec element. No content is permitted.
Only effective when used with a callout element. No content is permitted.
articleinfo is created if required for metadata. title, subtitle and titleabbrev created as required.
Only supported for use with blockquote. Must be preceded by blockquote or blockquote-title.
Child elements are defined using character styles. Any other text content is ignored.
Must be preceded by bibliography-title. title element created as required.
Must be preceded by bibliography-title. title element created as required.
Must be preceded by bibliography-title. title element created as required.
Consecutive blockquote elements are coalesced into a single blockquote element.
bookinfo is created if required for metadata. title, subtitle and titleabbrev created as required.
calloutlist element created automatically. Consecutive callout elements are coalesced into a single calloutlist element.
calloutlist element created automatically, see callout element.
Must be preceded by mediaobject, table or figure.
Consecutive cautions are colesced into a single caution element.
chapterinfo is created if required for metadata. title, subtitle and titleabbrev created as required.
Default element to use for metadata.
Created when a hyperlink refers to an email address.
Also created when text is marked-up as bold, italic or underlined. The role attribute encodes the weight or style used.
title element created as required. The immediately following block element is included in the example.
Created for images in the document.
Consecutive formal paragraphs are coalesced into a single formalpara element.
Consecutive elements are coalesced into a single highlights element.
Also creates imagedata element. The content of the paragraph becomes the value of the imagedata element's fileref attribute.
Also creates imagedata element. The content of the paragraph becomes the value of the imagedata element's fileref attribute.
Consecutive important paragraphs are coalesced into a single important element.
Created by index terms in the document.
imageobject and imagedata elements created as required.
Created for a table in the document.
Itemizedlist (bullet) list with nesting. Trailing digit refers to nesting level. Consecutive elements are coalesced into a single list element.
para-continue style paragraphs become separate paragraphs within a list item.
Line breaks are preserved in content. Consecutive literal layout paragraphs are coalesced into a single literallayoutelement.
Following image and/or text objects are included in the mediaobject element.
Following image object callout is included in the mediaobjectco.
Consecutive note paragraphs are coalesced into a single note element.
Orderedlist (number) list with nesting. Trailing digit refers to nesting level. Consecutive elements are coalesced into a single list element.
para-continue style paragraphs become separate paragraphs within a list item.
May be automatically created when required.
May be created automatically when required. Paragraphs without a style use this element.
partinfo element is created when required.
Line breaks within the content are preserved. Consecutive paragraphs are coalesced into a single programlisting element.
Line breaks within the content are preserved. Consecutive paragraphs are coalesced into a single programlistingco element.
Must be preceded by a qandaset-title.
Must be preceded by a qandaset-title. This element is created for a question element.
Must be preceded by qandaset-title. qandaentry element is created as required.
Revision data is specified by character styles. Any other content is discarded.
Must be preceded by revision paragraph.
Tables in the document are encoded using this element.
Creates a mediaobject and textdata elements as required. Immediately following paragraph becomes part of the text data.
Created as required for tables. See table.
Consecutive tip paragraphs are coalesced into a single tip element.
Consecutive terms are coalesced into a single variablelist. varlistentry elements are created as required.
Consecutive paragraphs are coalesced into a single warningelement.
